# Dark Mode in Tailwind CSS

The `dark:` variant applies styles when dark mode is active. Three strategies exist for activating it.

## Strategy 1: Media Query (Default)

Respects the user's OS preference via `prefers-color-scheme: dark`. No configuration needed.

```html
<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
  <h1 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Title</h1>
  <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Description</p>
  <button class="bg-indigo-600 dark:bg-indigo-500 text-white hover:bg-indigo-700 dark:hover:bg-indigo-400">
    Action
  </button>
</div>
```

This generates:
```css
.dark\:bg-gray-900 {
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    background-color: var(--color-gray-900);
  }
}
```

## Strategy 2: Class Toggle

Manually control dark mode with a CSS class on `<html>` or a parent element.

### v4 Configuration
```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@custom-variant dark (&:where(.dark, .dark *));
```

### v3 Configuration
```javascript
// tailwind.config.js
module.exports = {
  darkMode: "class",
};
```

### Usage
```html
<html class="dark">
  <body class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
    <!-- Dark mode active via class -->
  </body>
</html>
```

## Strategy 3: Data Attribute

Use a data attribute instead of a class:

### v4 Configuration
```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@custom-variant dark (&:where([data-theme=dark], [data-theme=dark] *));
```

### Usage
```html
<html data-theme="dark">
  <body class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
    <!-- Dark mode active via data attribute -->
  </body>
</html>
```

## Three-Way Toggle: Light / Dark / System

The most common real-world pattern — user picks light, dark, or respects OS.

### JavaScript (Add to `<head>` to prevent FOUC)
```html
<script>
  // Runs before paint to prevent flash of wrong theme
  document.documentElement.classList.toggle(
    "dark",
    localStorage.theme === "dark" ||
      (!("theme" in localStorage) &&
        window.matchMedia("(prefers-color-scheme: dark)").matches)
  );
</script>
```

### Toggle Functions
```javascript
// Light mode
function setLight() {
  localStorage.theme = "light";
  document.documentElement.classList.remove("dark");
}

// Dark mode
function setDark() {
  localStorage.theme = "dark";
  document.documentElement.classList.add("dark");
}

// System preference
function setSystem() {
  localStorage.removeItem("theme");
  const prefersDark = window.matchMedia("(prefers-color-scheme: dark)").matches;
  document.documentElement.classList.toggle("dark", prefersDark);
}
```

### Listen for OS Changes
```javascript
window.matchMedia("(prefers-color-scheme: dark)")
  .addEventListener("change", (e) => {
    if (!("theme" in localStorage)) {
      document.documentElement.classList.toggle("dark", e.matches);
    }
  });
```

## React Theme Switcher Component

```tsx
import { useEffect, useState } from "react";

type Theme = "light" | "dark" | "system";

export function ThemeSwitcher() {
  const [theme, setTheme] = useState<Theme>(() => {
    if (typeof window === "undefined") return "system";
    return (localStorage.getItem("theme") as Theme) ?? "system";
  });

  useEffect(() => {
    const root = document.documentElement;
    if (theme === "system") {
      localStorage.removeItem("theme");
      const prefersDark = window.matchMedia("(prefers-color-scheme: dark)").matches;
      root.classList.toggle("dark", prefersDark);
    } else {
      localStorage.setItem("theme", theme);
      root.classList.toggle("dark", theme === "dark");
    }
  }, [theme]);

  return (
    <select
      value={theme}
      onChange={(e) => setTheme(e.target.value as Theme)}
      className="rounded border border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-900 dark:text-white px-3 py-1.5"
    >
      <option value="light">Light</option>
      <option value="dark">Dark</option>
      <option value="system">System</option>
    </select>
  );
}
```

## Common Dark Mode Patterns

```html
<!-- Card with full dark mode support -->
<div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-6 shadow-sm dark:shadow-gray-900/20">
  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Card Title</h3>
  <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Description</p>
  <div class="mt-4 flex gap-3">
    <button class="bg-indigo-600 dark:bg-indigo-500 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-indigo-700 dark:hover:bg-indigo-400">
      Primary
    </button>
    <button class="border border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-700">
      Secondary
    </button>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Color Pairing Guide

| Light | Dark | Usage |
|-------|------|-------|
| `bg-white` | `dark:bg-gray-900` | Page background |
| `bg-gray-50` | `dark:bg-gray-800` | Card / surface |
| `text-gray-900` | `dark:text-white` | Primary text |
| `text-gray-600` | `dark:text-gray-400` | Secondary text |
| `text-gray-400` | `dark:text-gray-500` | Muted / placeholder |
| `border-gray-200` | `dark:border-gray-700` | Borders |
| `bg-indigo-600` | `dark:bg-indigo-500` | Primary action |
| `hover:bg-gray-50` | `dark:hover:bg-gray-700` | Hover surface |

## Debugging Dark Mode

1. **Not toggling?** Check `@custom-variant dark` (v4) or `darkMode: "class"` (v3) is set
2. **FOUC?** Put the theme detection script inline in `<head>`, before any stylesheets
3. **Variants not applying?** Ensure `.dark` class is on `<html>`, not `<body>`
4. **OS preference ignored?** If using class strategy, add matchMedia listener for system fallback
